						<summary>

						<p>Three fragments lying near the Parvatadēva temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Though the Report for the year 1962-63 has noticed three stone fragments, its published note [p. 138] is only on one piece. Since each piece seem to be different they have been identified here separately though the A.R. No. being the same].</p>						

						<p>This fragment-1 record in the 11th century A.D. characters is incomplete and contains only the genealogical account of Kāḷiseṭṭi partially and it seems, one of his ancestors made a gift, the account of which is not clear. This seems to be a Jaina record.</p>						

						</summary>
